      "stimulus_html": "",
      "stem_html": "<p>The <i>azide</i> functional group, which occurs in azidobenzene, contains three adjacent nitrogen atoms. One resonance structure for azidobenzene is shown. Draw three additional resonance structures, and assign appropriate formal charges to the atoms in all four.</p>\n<img class=\"scaled-down-30\" src=\"https://exercises.openstax.org/rails/active_storage/blobs/proxy/eyJfcmFpbHMiOnsibWVzc2FnZSI6IkJBaHBBcGtRIiwiZXhwIjpudWxsLCJwdXIiOiJibG9iX2lkIn19--56d26a1a44ab13914881d614ed00ef3df158d19a/OChem_02_EC_026.jpg\" alt=\"The structure of Azidobenzene features two lone pair on the nitrogen bonded to benzene and one lone pair on the terminal triple bonded nitrogen.\">",
